    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start. I think my students will grasp the real-world impact with those examples. I also want to make sure they understand why this is so important compared to just \"procedural\" due process. Could you add a part explaining why relying on just procedural due process isn't enough when it comes to protecting these fundamental rights?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is essential because it goes beyond mere procedural fairness; it actively protects our fundamental rights from government overreach. Procedural due process is like a safety net, ensuring fair procedures, but it doesn't always safeguard our core liberties. For instance, without substantive due process, the government could pass laws that infringe on our privacy or freedom of choice, even if the laws follow fair procedures. This principle is vital for maintaining a society where individual freedoms are respected and protected against arbitrary government actions. It's not just about following rules; it's about ensuring those rules don't trample on our essential rights.",
      "source": "target",
